subject: Volleyball
Olympic Games
Hazardous and Toxic Substances
Suicides and Suicide Attempts
lead_paragraph: Mike Whitmarsh, a 1996 Olympic silver medalist in beach volleyball, killed himself through carbon monoxide poisoning in the garage of a friend’s home, officials said. He was 46.
